============================================================
            AIRLINE RESERVATION SYSTEM
============================================================

Project Description:
--------------------
This project is a menu-driven Airline Reservation System
developed in the C programming language using binary file
handling (.dat files).

The system allows users to book airline tickets, select seats,
generate bills, modify or cancel reservations, while providing
an admin panel for flight management and financial reporting.

The project focuses on real-world problem solving using:
- Structures
- File handling
- Input validation
- Modular programming


------------------------------------------------------------
FEATURES
------------------------------------------------------------

USER MODULE:
------------
1. View available flights
2. Book airline tickets
3. Select seats with availability checking
4. Generate ticket/bill using PNR
5. Modify existing reservations
6. Cancel reservations

ADMIN MODULE:
-------------
1. Secure admin login
2. Add new flights
3. View all flights
4. Delete flights
5. View all reservations
6. Generate financial report
   - Total bookings
   - Total revenue
   - Average fare


------------------------------------------------------------
FILES USED
------------------------------------------------------------

flights.dat
-----------
Stores flight information in binary format.
Fields include:
- Flight Number
- Destination
- Departure City
- Departure Time
- Fare
- Available Seats

reservations.dat
----------------
Stores passenger reservation details in binary format.
Fields include:
- Passenger Name
- Age
- Gender
- Seat Number
- PNR
- Flight Number
- Fare
- Payment Method
- Booking Status


------------------------------------------------------------
TECHNOLOGIES USED
------------------------------------------------------------

Programming Language : C
File Handling        : Binary (.dat files)
Concepts Used        :
- Structures
- Functions
- File I/O (fread, fwrite)
- Input validation
- Menu-driven programming


------------------------------------------------------------
HOW TO RUN THE PROGRAM
------------------------------------------------------------

1. Compile the program:
   gcc airline.c -o airline

2. Run the executable:
   ./airline

3. On first run, the program will automatically create:
   - flights.dat
   - reservations.dat

4. Use Admin Menu to add flights before booking tickets.


------------------------------------------------------------
ADMIN LOGIN DETAILS
------------------------------------------------------------

Admin Password: admin123

(Note: Password is hardcoded for academic purposes only)


------------------------------------------------------------
IMPORTANT NOTES
------------------------------------------------------------

- .dat files are binary files and should not be edited manually.
- Flights must be added by the admin before users can book tickets.
- Seat availability is checked dynamically to prevent double booking.
- PNR is generated automatically and is unique per booking.


------------------------------------------------------------
LIMITATIONS
------------------------------------------------------------

- No user authentication system (single shared user space).
- No networking or database integration.
- Designed for academic and learning purposes only.


